passages.text: Key Takeaways from MBP Briefing: Targets 30% ROE in F3/31
Aims for F3/31 ROE target of \(30\%\) via ongoing shareholder returns to maintain equity at current level and improve medium- term earnings.

Medical Pharmaceuticals CDMO business in reach of MTP targets thanks to equipment installation at existing buildings and bigger workforce; construction of new building at Takatsuki Plant site around F3/31 should further boost production capacity.
Medical Pharmaceutical CDMO business: Headwinds for elective medical care recede; now focusing on boosting return on capital via efficiency gains (e.g., cutting CoGS, shrinking fixed assets).
Electronics: Anticipates growth via existing rigid substrate applications, with contributions also from FC- BGA and glass core substrate materials.

Management held the briefing on Aug 29 at 10:00 (JST). For semiconductor packages, although sales of FC- BGA applications are currently modest, they are expected to increase significantly around 2030 as product reputation grows. Glass core substrate materials have received positive feedback and are expected to contribute to earnings if the market takes off. Should the market fail to do so, management looks to achieve medium- term guidance via growth for components for organic materials. To reach its \(30\%\) ROE target (we estimate \(17\%\) in F3/26), the firm aims to grow profits while maintaining shareholder equity at around ¥100 bn. Assuming F3/31 OP of ¥47bn, financed non- operating income/expenses, a \(30\%\) tax rate, and an unchanged number of shares outstanding unchanged, we project EPS of ¥590. These earnings and shareholder returns developments should be a positive for the share price.
MORGAN STANLEY MUFG SECURITIES CO., LTD.

Our price target is based on our F3/27 EPS estimate and a P/E of 20x, which references the average of forward multiples for stocks we classify as semiconductor- related, plus a premium to account for higher profit growth certainty following the impairment of sales rights at Taiyo Pharma in the medical/pharma segment, shareholder returns based on consolidated TSR of \(100\%\) up to F3/28 at the earliest, and mid- term growth in the electronics segment.
Pkg & rigid (high- end) DF growth; accelerated pharma CDMO profit growth; LT listed drug risk shrinkage; effective M&A, tie- ups, 'sholder changes, TOBs/M&A, delisting, buybacks.

Weak profits in med/pharma on fewer production consignments, weaker demand for electronics; costs rise; stiff competition; yen strength; high- risk M&A, deteriorating stock supply/ demand on sell- offs.

Overweight (O). The stock's total return is expected to exceed the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Equal-weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Underweight (U). The stock's total return is expected to be below the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.
